theorem Topology.interior_diff_eq_diff_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    interior (A \ B : Set X) = A \ closure (B : Set X) := by
  classical
  -- We show the two inclusions separately.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` : from left to right.
    intro x hx
    -- From `hx` we know `x ∈ A \ B`.
    have h₁ : (x : X) ∈ A ∧ x ∉ B := by
      have : (x : X) ∈ (A \ B : Set X) := interior_subset hx
      simpa using this
    -- Extract the two components.
    rcases h₁ with ⟨hxA, hx_notB⟩
    -- Obtain an open neighbourhood of `x` contained in `A \ B`.
    rcases mem_interior.1 hx with ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUsub⟩
    -- Show that `x ∉ closure B`; otherwise `U ∩ B` would be non‐empty.
    have hxNotClB : (x : X) ∉ closure (B : Set X) := by
      by_contra hCl
      have hNonempty := (mem_closure_iff).1 hCl U hUopen hxU
      have hContr : (U ∩ B : Set X) = ∅ := by
        apply Set.eq_empty_of_subset_empty
        intro y hy
        have : y ∈ A \ B := hUsub hy.1
        exact hy.2 this.2
      simpa [hContr] using hNonempty
    -- Conclude that `x ∈ A \ closure B`.
    exact ⟨hxA, hxNotClB⟩
  · -- `⊇` : from right to left.
    intro x hx
    -- Split the membership in `A \ closure B`.
    rcases hx with ⟨hxA, hxNotClB⟩
    -- The complement of `closure B` is an open neighbourhood of `x`.
    have hUopen : IsOpen (closure (B : Set X))ᶜ :=
      isClosed_closure.isOpen_compl
    have hxU : (x : X) ∈ (closure (B : Set X))ᶜ := by
      simpa using hxNotClB
    -- Intersect this neighbourhood with `A`, which is open.
    have hVopen : IsOpen (A ∩ (closure (B : Set X))ᶜ) :=
      hA.inter hUopen
    have hxV : (x : X) ∈ A ∩ (closure (B : Set X))ᶜ := ⟨hxA, hxU⟩
    -- This open set is contained in `A \ B`.
    have hVsub : (A ∩ (closure (B : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ A \ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact ⟨hy.1, by
        have : (y : X) ∈ (closure (B : Set X))ᶜ := hy.2
        have : y ∉ closure (B : Set X) := this
        intro hyB
        have : (y : X) ∈ closure (B : Set X) :=
          subset_closure hyB
        exact (this.2 this).elim⟩
    -- Hence `x` belongs to the interior of `A \ B`.
    exact mem_interior.2 ⟨_, hVopen, hxV, hVsub⟩

theorem Topology.closure_iInter_subset_iInter_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {ι : Sort _} (F : ι → Set X) :
    closure (⋂ i, F i : Set X) ⊆ ⋂ i, closure (F i) := by
  intro x hx
  have h : ∀ i, x ∈ closure (F i) := by
    intro i
    have hSub : (⋂ j, F j : Set X) ⊆ F i := by
      intro y hy
      exact (Set.mem_iInter.1 hy) i
    exact (closure_mono hSub) hx
  exact Set.mem_iInter.2 h
